RY","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recDQBURWk06n8iqB","target":"recE7gMJ0r4eJWepx","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recDQBURWk06n8iqB","target":"rec31pLZApXuca8pm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recDQBURWk06n8iqB","target":"recdU0shMzVelyTiU","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recDQBURWk06n8iqB","target":"recxpkcBPRCLBgtu1","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recDQBURWk06n8iqB","target":"recKRsEFLaEueJvei","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recNtazRWS89XSXQx","ref":"1Sam.25.1","text":"And Samuel died; and all the Israelites were gathered together, and lamented him, and buried him in his house at Ramah. And David arose, and went down to the wilderness of Paran.","year":-1060},{"id":"rec5nhAkRht1Hd9Ms","ref":"1Sam.25.2","text":"And there was a man in Maon, whose possessions were in Carmel; and the man was very great, and he had three thousand sheep, and a thousand goats: and he was shearing his sheep in Carmel.","year":-1060},{"id":"recTCeCWwIkKlhXP6","ref":"1Sam.25.3","text":"Now the name of the man was Nabal; and the name of his wife Abigail: and she was a woman of good understanding, and of a beautiful countenance: but the man was churlish and evil in his doings; and he was of the house of Caleb.","year":-1060},{"id":"recSxwDCtP0r6ZELW","ref":"1Sam.25.4","text":"And David heard in the wilderness that Nabal did shear his sheep.","year":-1060},{"id":"recVtC83NYyy4GNqu","ref":"1Sam.25.5","text":"And David sent out ten young men, and David said unto the young men, Get you up to Carmel, and go to Nabal, and greet him in my name:","year":-1060},{"id":"recKj8ONjVphQ6VRy","ref":"1Sam.25.6","text":"And thus shall ye say to him that liveth in prosperity, Peace be both to thee, and peace be to thine house, and peace be unto all that thou hast.","year":-1060},{"id":"recHCYgSrTS7cW6Vy","ref":"1Sam.25.7","text":"And now I have heard that thou hast shearers: now thy shepherds which were with us, we hurt them not, neither was there ought missing unto them, all the while they were in Carmel.","year":-1060},{"id":"recyjNXpv5dWJkwLJ","ref":"1Sam.25.8","text":"Ask thy young men, and they will shew thee. Wherefore let the young men find favour in thine eyes: for we come in a good day: give, I pray thee, whatsoever cometh to thine hand unto thy servants, and to thy son David.","year":-1060}]}
